<font color="#FF0000">POLITICS AS USUAL</font><br>
<tt>Sun Jan 25 16:53:31 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
Good thoughts. I have a different take on Al Gore. To me<br>
he is one of the more principled politicians out there.<br>
An angel he ain't but better than most, which is not saying much.<br><br>
Cook you said &quot;This time we oppose it before the war, but once <br>
committed, we support the troops.&quot;. I am not sure what you<br>
mean by this. Is it possible to support the troups and<br>
at the same time oppose the war? Can one support the troups<br>
by trying to bring them home? I think one can, without<br>
sacraficing the safety of the troupos while they are on the ground.<br><br>
As to the assumption that one has to have gone to war to<br>
be a president able to make the decision to lead our<br>
nation in war. I disagree. I think that sometimes what<br>
we really need is a president that has not gone to war,<br>
and that does not see war as aviable alternative except<br>
in the extreme. <br><br>
Once we are at that point of making a decision, he/she must<br>
use all the resources at hand to help guide us in the<br>
decision about going to war. Once we are in a war, it <br>
is essential that we seperate the tactics of warfare from<br>
the tactics of politics and re-election.<br><br>
DO NOT READ THIS AS AN ENDORSMENT OF SLICK WILLEY. I actually<br>
think that having been to war is only one of the things we need<br>
to look at when choosing a president. It is secondary in<br>
comparison to having a morality, being honest, truthful,<br>
and principled. It is secondary to being a person who has not<br>
sold out to special interests. <br><br>
Given the state of politics in the US I don't think that<br>
such a person could get elected. The media presentation<br>
controls how people view presidential candidates. That takes<br>
money, BIG MONEY. To get big money you need to be willing<br>
to sell out. That is why we need a different electoral<br>
process, that is not subject to being bought and sold to<br>
the highest bidder. That is why Bull Clinton, Newt G,<br>
Al G., Steve Forbes or any of those people will not make a<br>
difference. They are all sell outs.<br><br>
I propose Cook Barela for president.  While I disagree with Cook on<br>
many many things, he is certainly more honest than<br>
anyone who is presently running, and is willing to listen<br>
(after someone hits him upside the head two or three times).<br><br>
Damn. Here we are looking at another possible war and we<br>
can't tell what decisions are made with the U.S. people in<br>
mind and what decisions are made to protect our President's<br>
arse. Don't it make you mad.
